# Caddy reverse proxy → automatic HTTPS for Alpha Terminal.
# Browsers only allow installable PWAs + Web Push over a secure context, so this
# terminates TLS and proxies to the app.
#
# ALPHA_DOMAIN controls the cert behavior (set it in .env):
#   • a real domain you own (e.g. alpha.example.com) → Caddy auto-provisions a
#     trusted Let's Encrypt cert (needs ports 80/443 reachable + DNS pointed here).
#   • localhost or a LAN IP (the default) → Caddy issues a local self-signed cert
#     from its internal CA. Install Caddy's root CA on your phone to make it
#     trusted, or use Tailscale (see README) for valid certs with no domain.

{$ALPHA_DOMAIN} {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy alpha:8787
}
